### Built-in helpers ​
`string()`, `number()`, `boolean()`, `url()`, `email()`, `oneOf([...])`, `json<T>()` cover the common cases.
Each helper returns a Standard Schema-conformant builder with `.optional()` and `.default(value)` modifiers.
For richer validation (regex, transforms, branded types), drop in any Standard Schema library — valibot, zod, or arktype work out of the box, and you can mix them with the built-ins:
ts
```
import * as v from 'valibot';
export default defineEnv({
STRIPE_KEY: string(), // built-in
WEBHOOK_URL: v.pipe(v.string(), v.url(), v.endsWith('/webhook')), // valibot
});
```
